Commentary: Sohail Tanvir to Asad Shafiq, no run, starts on a full length, gets his natural away movement. Easily played into the off side, towards cover
Sohail Tanvir to Asad Shafiq, 1 run, a tad straighter, still full. Not much swing. Just a little bit of away seam movement, outside-edged down to third man
Sohail Tanvir to Ahmed Shehzad, 1 run, nice stroke. A tad short this time, short and wide. Scythed down to third man for a run. Played that late
Sohail Tanvir to Asad Shafiq, 1 run
Sohail Tanvir to Ahmed Shehzad, 1 run, good stuff. Full again, in a good channel just outside off, carved down to third man with an angled bat
Sohail Tanvir to Asad Shafiq, no run, straying down leg, rapped on the pad. Full delivery on Shafiq's pads, he fails to make contact. An optimistic appeal is quickly aborted
Mohammad Irfan to Ahmed Shehzad, no run, a bit of a whirry action. Full and straight to start, defended towards mid-off
Mohammad Irfan to Ahmed Shehzad, 1 leg bye, on the pads again, Shehzad misses a flick. Off the pad towards square leg
Mohammad Irfan to Asad Shafiq, 1 run, too straight yet again, worked away through square leg for one
Mohammad Irfan to Ahmed Shehzad, 1 run, lovely line, but well played too. Full and straight, prodded away towards cover for a quick run
Mohammad Irfan to Asad Shafiq, FOUR, goes over mid-on this time. Again, full. Again, straight. Predictable. Shafiq goes up and over mid-on. Easy
Mohammad Irfan to Asad Shafiq, no run, looks to go over again, fails to time it. Full outside off. Shafiq mis-times his drive to mid-off
Sohail Tanvir to Ahmed Shehzad, no run, nice line, nagging away around off, blocked

Sohail Tanvir to Ahmed Shehzad, 2 runs, good length around middle, jabbed to midwicket for a couple. But is he quick enough? Shafiq needed a full-length dive and that saved him. Kept the bat face pointing up. Good effort from Shafiq.

Sohail Tanvir to Ahmed Shehzad, OUT, given! A bouncer down leg, Shehzad tries to get outside the line and help the ball down to fine leg. But can't get bat on his stroke, just glove. A simple catch for the keeper and Lahore strike! Beaten by some extra bounce
Wicket: ['Ahmed Shehzad c †Mohammad Rizwan b Sohail Tanvir 5 (8b 0x4 0x6) SR: 62.50']

Commentary: Sohail Tanvir to Pietersen, 2 runs, comes down to Tanvir and flamingo-flicks him through midwicket for a couple. Proactive stuff from KP. Lovely shot, great timing
Sohail Tanvir to Pietersen, 1 leg bye, big appeal. On the pads, KP misses a flick, the ball ricochets towards short fine leg. Pitched way outside leg
Sohail Tanvir to Asad Shafiq, no run, full and wide outside off, slapped away with bad timing to cover.
Narine to Pietersen, no run, the carrom ball to start. Full outside off, KP looks to turn the ball through midwicket, but gets a leading edge to cover
Narine to Pietersen, no run, short and wide this time, slashed to extra cover
Narine to Pietersen, 1 run, a touch straighter and fuller, Pietersen nails his sweep to deep backward square leg
Narine to Asad Shafiq, FOUR, a slog sweep! Tossed up on off, Shafiq gets low and pounces all over his sweep. Just beats midwicket, the fielder at the boundary makes a mess of his dive
Narine to Asad Shafiq, no run, gives himself room this time, full and straight, hit away to mid-off. Bad timing
Narine to Asad Shafiq, no run, gets waaay outside off stump and misses his sweep. The bowling team inexplicably goes up in appeal. No run
Mohammad Irfan to Pietersen, no run, nicely played. Full delivery outside off, hit up to mid-off with great timing. Doesn't find the gap

Mohammad Irfan to Pietersen, OUT, inside-edged into the stumps. A massive wicket. Pietersen runs at the bowler and wipes his bat through the line. There is a bit of inward seam movement though and the ball takes the inside edge and whacks leg stump. One of the Gladiators' best batsman.
Mohammad Irfan to Rossouw, 1 run, good length outside off, pushed away towards cover from the crease
Mohammad Irfan to Asad Shafiq, no run, just struggling with timing are these batsmen. There is some natural movement too. Full on off and middle, swiped to midwicket
Mohammad Irfan to Asad Shafiq, no run, full outside off, comes down again and drives hard to mid-off
Mohammad Irfan to Asad Shafiq, no run, lovely change in pace. A slower delivery on middle, Shafiq is way too early through his pull and is hit on the body. Clever bowling
Narine to Rossouw, no run, flat and wide, driven away towards point
Narine to Rossouw, 1 run, drops short on off, Rossouw goes back and slaps his pull to mid-on. A naughty fumble allows one
Narine to Asad Shafiq, 1 run, falls just short of midwicket. Flat on off, Shafiq gets across, looks to hit over square leg but toe-ends it almost to deep midwicket
Narine to Rossouw, no run, good length. Flat and straight, pushed back
Narine to Rossouw, 1 run, a good single, push and run to cover
Narine to Asad Shafiq, no run, another nasty wipe across the line. Slow down leg, Shafiq gives himself room, Narine follows him. Beaten
Bilawal Bhatti to Rossouw, 1 run, shortish and wide, nailed to the deep sweeper cover fielder
Bilawal Bhatti to Asad Shafiq, no run, runs down at the bowler. Good length on middle, Shafiq advances and mis-times a pull back to the bowler. Looking for muscle, not timing, not his strength
Bilawal Bhatti to Asad Shafiq, FOUR, he'll get four this time. Not the greatest looking stroke. A slower bouncer outside off, Shafiq gets a top edge which flies in the gap at backward square leg
Bilawal Bhatti to Asad Shafiq, no run, good length on off, hammered back to the bowler

Bilawal Bhatti to Asad Shafiq, 1 run, no run there. What? Short and wide, pushed to short cover. Shafiq calls for one, puts his partner in jeopardy too. The fielder misses the stumps at the bowler's end. Out by a distance if he hit

Bilawal Bhatti to Rossouw, 2 runs, bat goes over square leg. Waaaatch out! The third umpire is called for. The ball went somewhere towards midwicket. While everyone was looking at the bat, the batsmen complete two. The bat handle is in Rossouw's hand, the rest of his bat isn't. They have plenty of replacements these days. Rossouw's foot is inside the crease, plenty of replays.
Yasir Shah to Asad Shafiq, FOUR, that's better from Shafiq. Stick to his strengths. One of them is his touch. He gets low and reverse-paddles the ball down to the third man boundary. Fantastic
Yasir Shah to Asad Shafiq, 1 run, the hard sweep this time, earns him one to deep square leg
Yasir Shah to Rossouw, 1 run, tossed up outside off, drilled down to long-off
Yasir Shah to Asad Shafiq, 1 run, flat outside off, Shafiq runs down and flicks to deep square leg. One
Yasir Shah to Rossouw, 1 run, another nice paddle reverse sweep. Flat on off, played with soft hands to short third man
Yasir Shah to Asad Shafiq, no run, short and wide, crashed straight to cover
Bilawal Bhatti to Rossouw, 1 run, good length on off, looks to hit that to long-on. Mis-timed to long-off
Bilawal Bhatti to Asad Shafiq, 3 runs, poor delivery. Short and wide, cut in front of point for a couple. There is an overthrow too. Three the result
Bilawal Bhatti to Rossouw, no run, shortish and straight, Rossouw flat-bats the ball back to the bowler. Bad timing again
Bilawal Bhatti to Rossouw, 1 run, nice slower delivery, good length on off. Mis-timed away towards point
Bilawal Bhatti to Asad Shafiq, 2 runs, there goes McCullum with an acrobatic dive. A low full toss outside off, driven wide of cover for a couple. Just out of reach of Baz
Bilawal Bhatti to Asad Shafiq, 1 run, bad delivery. Short down leg, pulled down to fine leg for one. Lucky to get away with that

Narine to Asad Shafiq, OUT, and gets a wicket with his first ball. Full and straight from Narine, Shafiq gets low, looks to paddle the ball down to fine leg. Fails to make any connection and the stumps light up. A struggling innings ends
Narine to Sarfraz Ahmed, 1 run, poor ball, gets away with it. Short and wide from Narine, cut away but straight to backward point
Narine to Rossouw, no run, shortish outside off, pushed away to cover
Narine to Rossouw, no run, on the pads this time, length down leg, Rossouw misses a flick. Hit on the pad
Narine to Rossouw, 1 run, a tad full this time, drilled down to long-off

Narine to Sarfraz Ahmed, OUT, huge wicket this. Sarfraz goes. Slow delivery outside off, it's short too. Sarfraz sees the length and decides to cut. The offbreak rips in, takes the inside edge and then clatters into the stumps. Poor shot selection. Excellent captaincy from McCullum to have Narine bowl one here.
Yasir Shah to Rossouw, 1 run, Rossouw runs down and heaves one to deep midwicket. Not great timing
Yasir Shah to Mohammad Nawaz, no run, well bowled. Pushed wide outside off, Nawaz leaves.
Yasir Shah to Mohammad Nawaz, 1 run, on the pads, flicked down to short fine leg
Yasir Shah to Rossouw, no run, nice. Slower through the air, straight, pushed back
Yasir Shah to Rossouw, no run, runs down, Yasir fires the ball outside off, inside-edged into the pad
Yasir Shah to Rossouw, no run, short again, wide. Hammered to cover. Another dot. Just two of the over. Good stuff.

Elliott to Mohammad Nawaz, OUT, out? Direct hit and that should be No.5. On a length outside off, carved to point. The fielder picks up cleanly and throws the stumps down at the bowler's end. Fantastic fielding. Elliott got in front of the stumps, but let the ball hit the stumps. The Qalandars have been on point today
Elliott to Rossouw, no run, slower ball outside off, mis-timed back to the bowler
Elliott to Rossouw, 1 run, driven away to deep cover for one
Elliott to Perera, 1 run, another offcutter outside off, so slow. Inside-edged towards midwicket. Pace off ruling the contest
Elliott to Rossouw, 1 run, well bowled. Pace off again, the ball stops on Rossouw, a checked drive makes its way to midwicket. So slow this surface
Elliott to Perera, 1 run, overpitched outside off, driven to cover. Another tidy over ticks by
Narine to Perera, 1 run, short and wide, crashed out to deep point
Narine to Rossouw, 1 run, slow outside off, worked to deep midwicket nicely, just one though
Narine to Perera, no run, darted in on off, the offbreak, defended
Narine to Perera, 1 run, shortish and a tad too wide, drilled out to deep cover for one
Narine to Rossouw, 1 run, a reverse lap to short third man for a run
Narine to Perera, 1 run, pushed down to long-off. End of a fantastic spell of T20 bowling. 4-0-16-2
Elliott to Perera, 1 run, a low full toss, hit down to long-off for one
Elliott to Rossouw, SIX, that's a nice stroke. Too much width from Elliott. Rossouw gets low and hammers a lofted drive over cover. Superb timing
Elliott to Rossouw, 2 runs, a bouncer. Short delivery on off and middle, Rossouw feigned a lap sweep, then executed an upper cut over third man for some runs
Elliott to Rossouw, 1 run, hit to the deep extra cover fielder for one
Elliott to Perera, FOUR, four more. Getting a move along now. Length outside off, hammered past cover and that will be four
Elliott to Perera, 1 run, punched to long-off for one. A good over that, 15 runs from it
Yasir Shah to Perera, 1 run, fired in on middle, pushed to long-on. "Keeper's end," yells Rizwan. The second isn't attempted
Yasir Shah to Rossouw, 1 run, shortish delivery on middle, scythed away to deep point

Yasir Shah to Perera, OUT, taken. Bhatti takes the catch at long-off, a nonchalant attempt but doesn't matter if you take them. Yasir tossed that googly up, inviting a heave. Thisara can't stop himself, skews the ball off the outside half and an easy catch is accepted
Yasir Shah to Rossouw, 1 run, flat delivery outside off, tapped to short third man
Yasir Shah to Hasan Khan, 1 run, nicely driven to long-off with the spin

Yasir Shah to Rossouw, FOUR, uh oh. Naughty fielding. Flat outside off, Rossouw gets a thick outside edge which races down past short third man. Irfan can't get his hand down the ball, concedes a couple extra runs
Sohail Tanvir to Hasan Khan, 1 run, a length delivery on off, played down to third man for one
Sohail Tanvir to Rossouw, 1 run, on a length outside off, dabbed down to third man
Wicket: ['NLTC Perera c Bilawal Bhatti b Yasir Shah 12 (11b 1x4 0x6) SR: 109.09']

Commentary: Sohail Tanvir to Hasan Khan, 1 run, another neat dab down to third man for a run
Sohail Tanvir to Rossouw, FOUR, runs down and gets the ball past mid-off. Knew which area he wanted to attack and executed well. Hammered a slower delivery past mid-off
Sohail Tanvir to Rossouw, FOUR, four more! Advances down and inside-edges his heave past the stumps for four. Fortuitous, but Gladiators will not care
Sohail Tanvir to Rossouw, 1 run, slower ball on off, pushed down to mid-on
Yasir Shah to Rossouw, 1 run, sees Rossouw coming, fires this on middle, pushed to long-on
Yasir Shah to Hasan Khan, 1 run, good single, pushed to McCullum at cover and Rossouw sets off. Should not have been one there
Yasir Shah to Rossouw, 1 run, flat on middle, a mis-timed reverse sweep to short third man
Yasir Shah to Hasan Khan, no run, better from McCullum. Flat delivery outside off, hit to cover. No run
Yasir Shah to Hasan Khan, SIX, comes down and gets enough on his drive to clear the fielder. Not quite to the pitch but he had enough to get the ball over the fielder at long-on. Nice clean stroke
Yasir Shah to Hasan Khan, FOUR, four more. Short and wide this time, scythed to deep point for four
Mohammad Irfan to Rossouw, SIX, huge! Short delivery on middle, Rossouw hammers his pull and it clears the fielder at midwicket. Fantastic batting
Mohammad Irfan to Rossouw, 2 runs, hit nicely past cover for a couple more. Fifty for Rossouw. Fantastic rearguard effort this
Mohammad Irfan to Rossouw, 1 run, overpitched outside off, mis-timed to long-off. Just the one this time
Mohammad Irfan to Hasan Khan, 1 run, lovely batting. A yorker on off, opens the face late to get that in front of point. Just one
Mohammad Irfan to Rossouw, 1 run, full and straight, Rossouw can't quire get underneath that. One to long-on
Mohammad Irfan to Hasan Khan, no run, good finish. A yorker on off, hit towards cover. Dot. Good over for Quetta
Sohail Tanvir to Rossouw, no run, well bowled. A slow bouncer outside off. Rossouw tries to cut over point but doesn't make contact
Sohail Tanvir to Rossouw, 1 run, excellent delivery. Yorker outside off, jammed away towards McCullum at cover.
Sohail Tanvir to Hasan Khan, 1 run, full and straight, mis-timed to long-on for one.
Sohail Tanvir to Rossouw, 1 run, a slower ball on middle, Rossouw mis-times his heave to deep midwicket. Lovely change in pace

Sohail Tanvir to Hasan Khan, OUT, slower ball on middle again. Hasan climbed into his mow, but doesn't get enough on that. Timing is hard on this surface, Hasan picks out deep midwicket. Superb over this so far
Sohail Tanvir to Rossouw, 1 run, excellent over that. Just four off it. Slower ball outside off, jammed away to long-off for a run.
Mohammad Irfan to Rossouw, 2 runs, how did he get that there? Looks for a lap sweep over short fine leg, gets the ball over the keeper for a couple.
Mohammad Irfan to Rossouw, 2 runs, swiped away through midwicket. Full and straight from Irfan. The fielder at long-on dives to his left and saves a couple. Good effort

Mohammad Irfan to Rossouw, OUT, taken at long-on. End of an excellent innings that from Rossouw. Full on middle and off, right in the arc. Rossouw gets underneath it nicely, but gets more elevation than distance. Umar Akmal takes a well-judged catch at long-on
Mohammad Irfan to Anwar Ali, 2 runs, nice stuff. Full and straight, hammered to long-off for a couple. The fielder dives to his right to save a couple more
Mohammad Irfan to Anwar Ali, 1 run, a yorker on off, squirted away to deep midwicket, just one more
Wicket: ['Hasan Khan c Roy b Sohail Tanvir 16 (11b 1x4 1x6) SR: 145.45']

Commentary: Mohammad Irfan to Mills, OUT, a yorker on leg, Mills misses his slog and is struck right in front of leg stump. Given. Replays show the ball was missing leg stump.
